In the reoriented reference frame [mathjaxinline]\vec{r}_{\rm s} = x_{\rm s} \hat{\imath }[/mathjaxinline]. 
Let's choose to find [mathjaxinline]\vec{B}[/mathjaxinline] at positions on the [mathjaxinline]z[/mathjaxinline]-axis; 
then the field coordinate is [mathjaxinline]\vec{r}_{\rm f} =z_{\rm f} \hat{k}[/mathjaxinline], and

[mathjax]\vec{B} =-\frac{\mu _0 I}{4 \pi z_{\rm f}} \int _{-a}^{a} \! \! \!
        \cos \theta \,  d\theta \, \, \hat{\jmath } = -\frac{\mu _0 I}{2 \pi z_{\rm f}} \frac{a}{\sqrt {a^2+z_{\rm f}^2} }\;  
        \hat{\jmath }.[/mathjax]
